annotation.TEXT: Umm... Why is there suddenly a shiny clump of green dirt lodged in between the pipes here? That wasn't there before, and there's no way to reach it, I don't think...
Oh, farfignewton!

Oh, and this green pipe used to be the exit from that shortcut that was present in the previous version of this level. Actually, I wonder if that shortcut is still here... I'll have to replay the level to check.
So, has anything changed in Yellow Switch? Let's find out.
Oh, d'oh! The last Yoshi coin was right there! Wait, maybe I can still reach it...
Hmm... This is still only about eight and a half minutes of mostly recycled content, so... You know what? I'll go for a little length on today's episode and toss in Tiger's walk too!
And there's our secret exit, same as before.
And this time, I kept Mario's head out of the way so you can properly see the word "places".
Alright, let's move on with the level now.
Also, I think this line of coins leading down from the clouds should be adjusted so that the player can reasonably grab them all in one jump.
And there's that tall ledge and that shell that I want to fry again.
Alright, let's start with Yoshi's House and see what's been adjusted.

Huh. There's now an upside-down pipe in the sky... or was that there before? Also, if you screen scroll to the left from here, you can see the cage that those Goombas started in. (I'm sure that cage was there before, except it held red koopas previously.)
Mario, now's not the time to get hammered...
There's now munchers up here, and the flower is now on a cement block, and there's now a MOOOONNN!!! YES YES YES!!!

...and it causes me to come out of the upside-down pipe directly above. Umm... Okay... What was the point of that? I mean, sure, it refreshes the level, but this doesn't seem like a place that needs a reset pipe...

Alright, I'm glad this Yoshi coin setup remained unchanged. However, if only the top and bottom cannons of each column actually fire, maybe you should change the middle cannons into cement blocks or bottoms of the upper cannons.
Insanity speed boost!
There was Yoshi coin number four (which I could fortunately reach from this side).
Yep, that pipe and piranha plant are still up there too. Greenman, is there a point to those things, or is there actually a way to reach them that I didn't find yet?
The rest of the ? blocks, including the two power up blocks, are the same, so I wonder what's with this random key addition here...
Wha...? A key? That wasn't there before...
What, really? This pipe goes nowhere? Well, I can use it to safely collect all of the coins making up this bridge, but that can't have been its intended use, right?
Sweet!

Well, I've done quite a bit today, and I hope nearly 14 minutes of mostly recycled content is good enough for this episode. But, what changes could've been made to the Tight rope walking event? Find out next time!
Seems about the same so far, including this Banzai Bill that just wants to get in my face here.
Gah! Freaking Chuck! Wow, he jumped unexpectedly fast after appearing!
Oh, man. Runnin' on gray platforms.
Moon count: 1 (Note: The moon count has been reset for this hack's version 2.)
Oh, that koopa's lost his shell, which removes the easy life-farming spot here.

I notice the last power up block that used to be just in front of the goal has been removed. (Actually, you could've left the ? block there, but changed it to produce a coin or multiple coins instead.)
Oh, but I'm going to have to be a bit clever here...
The keyhole is still there, but is that pipe perhaps a way to get out of here in case you fell in without the key?
There's a Baseball Chuck that wasn't there before.
Okay, now let's see what's different in A Starting Journey...
Ha! Now, is that door still there?
I thought about ending the episode here, but just six minutes of mostly recycled content didn't seem like it would make for a decent video, so let's include Well on the way in this episode too!
There's now a Lava Lotus up here in the clouds that wasn't here before.
Alright, now to quickly go back for the secret exit...
Well, for starters, there's now a Pokey here that wasn't here before.
Okay, this pipe is still enterable...
Shut up, clock. I'm done with the level anyway.
It sure is, and...
To be continued...

Hey there, guys! I'm back to the Island of... Oh, it actually says "Insanity" on the title screen now! Yeah, so Greenman1147 made an update, and now I'm going to play through it and see what's changed. The title demo and intro screen are no different, however, so I'll just speed through them.
I just know it did that on purpose just to mess with my mind... game... mind... game...
Oh, right. I need to bring a P-switch with me. Thank goodness this still isn't one of those insanely evil Kaizo hacks that doesn't let you go back for one!
Awesome.

And the level appears to end the same way as before. Well, this level only had a couple of minor changes in the second half, but those changes did fix an obvious level break and make one Yoshi coin a little trickier to reach.
Oh? I do believe I saw something down there in this pit below the hammer duder...
Go my yellow blocks! Go and conquer the world with your yellowy-ness! (Did I spell "yellowy-ness" right, or is it actually spelled "yellowiness"?)
Also, I fail at block cloning today. Also, none of these blocks were power ups?
Ooh, I saw another pipe in that pit where the keyhole was before.
There are no longer P-switch coins on the lowest four rows. Also, I'm going to try to take a little shortcut here...
Seems like a strange addition if you ask me...
Ah, so does this lead to a new bonus room?
Okay, one more hit...
Also, the first power up block was moved for some reason. Now, is there anything different regarding this P-switch?
There's the last Yoshi coin, and suddenly, a cement block that screws with the 1-up combo I used to be able to get here.
What, goombas? Yeah, no koopas here either, probably so I couldn't try to take advantage of that old life-farming spot again!
Yes! But, I might've wasted too much time getting it, and I might be doomed here now!
Aha! These cannons aren't taking me by surprise this time! Also, do only the bottom two fire? If so, what's the point of the rest of them stretching up into the sky?
Gotta aim my shots carefully here without getting any baseballs lodged in my brain.
But, without that P-switch, how can I make that door appear now? Well, there are more P-switches in the level later on...
I'm expecting one of these blocks to be a power up block...
This P-switch setup is still the same, except for one thing...
Okay, whew! I was still able to make it to solid ground in time!
So, what's changed in this level?
Ooh, the cement ceiling up here has been extended to the left! Now I can't simply break the level with a simple normal jump!
Heh, floating munchers when I hit a P-switch. Maybe they should be placed on cement blocks as well.
Huh. This shell-in-a-box is still here for some reason. Greenman, is there any real purpose for this shell?
Mario? Are you still hammered?
GAAAMMMEEE!!!
Also, oh, man. Life-farming spot!

Maybe what you should do is change that P-switch door into an enterable pipe that's covered with brown blocks, and make it lead to an interesting and rewarding bonus room. Then, perhaps have it come out here near the goal.
Well, it doesn't look like this place has changed at all...
And there's the last Yoshi coin. It's a no-brainer to get, but at least this level now has five Yoshi coins.
I'm not going to speed up any of this footage though, since I'll stop the shell as soon as the first 1-up appears.
Huh. The power up block just after midpoint has been changed to a coin block for some reason (I don't think that change was necessary), and the fifth Yoshi coin is no longer right there either.
There's now a gray pipe in the pit down here. That's totally gotta lead somewhere, so let me just wait for the P-switch to expire...
Okay, so let's go back and look for that shortcut... (I'll speed up some of this footage.)
Green with envy?
Oh, yeah. I remember now. There used to be a P-switch up in the clouds here, and hitting it made a door appear just after midpoint.
There doesn't seem to be anything of value way up there either... Ah, but down here, there do appear to be some additional enemies!
Awesome. Those typos have been corrected. Now I can take this message seriously again. Alright, Yoshi, I'm backing away now. I don't want any trouble.
I would like to bring the springboard out of here with me, for backtracking purposes... if the game will let me...
Well, there's seaweed coming out of the floor from the start of the level now...
Ooh! Save prompt right away this time! I guess that means you made the Yellow Switch a "no-auto-move" level, right?
Ah, new Yoshi coin here. Does that mean this level now has a total of five? We'll find out later, but first, I want to check something earlier in the level...
Okay, that's not what I was expecting, but sure, that works. Now a player won't have to worry about being trapped in the keyhole pit!
...it still works the same way. However, it took previous knowledge of that door's existence and some clever coin collecting to make use of the shortcut this time, so this feels a bit unrewarding...
Bah. So much for that shortcut idea.
No, it leads to the old bonus room? That's weird...
So, if the pipe in the pit below the hammer duder goes to the old bonus room, does that mean the gray pipe that used to go there is non-functional now?
Wow, that's a lot of Chucks. Well, you certainly made this previously empty area more interesting...
Well, I can't seem to enter the upside-down sky pipe. I'm pretty sure this pipe down here still works though, but I'll hold off on checking the side area for a moment.
And there's still not nearly enough koopas to get a 1-up combo with.
Barf! I've gotta stop with the stupid mistakes...
I still don't know what the deal is with the tall ledge with the pipe and piranha plant on it in the first half, though.
Oh, man. Lag.
Oh, but this note block is now five tiles high instead of six, making it much easier to jump onto!
That Yoshi coin's new. Now I just need one more...
